title: For Sale/Trade:  For Sale: 30 rds 5.56 NATO .223 AR15 AR-15 M-193 Ammo Lake City Federal 55 gr brass
postcontent:
30 rounds of 5.56x45 XM-193 55 gr. Lake City Federal ammo manufacture date of Oct 2012.
That is exactly one 30 rd magazine worth of the best ammo you could feed an AR15! I have 1000 rds available.
These are the exact same rounds the US ARMY usesI Except, in most cases they use the 62 gr. M-855 which has the steel penetrator. That's because they are in a fight where the enemy might have body armor. But most people aren't looking for something to penetrate armor - they are looking for something that will kill a badguy, or a watermelon. The M-193 is the best round for that task. I just happened to buy a few thousand rounds a couple of months before this whole thing kicked off. But now, there's a whole lot of guys who have new rifles, new magazines, but no ammo. I will sell you some of my stockpile. It's going to be (pre freak out) expensive. But since you can't get any 5.56/.223 ammo anywhere, this is a bargain. I just want to see EVERYONE able to load up now. No sense owning a rifle and not having any ammo. I will not sell my entire stash. BTW, you should have prepared earlier. But then again, isn't that always the case...

Just in case you are new to owning AR15s, check your barrel and make sure it is stamped either 5.56 or 5.56/.223. If all you see is .223 - Then do not buy this ammo. Although it probably won't kill you, you should not shoot 5.56 through a .223 only barrel. LuckyGunner Labs did a story on this. You can Google it.

For everyone who thinks I'm price gouging, I don't think that definition applies. I am offering up some of my personal supplies at a price that makes it worth it to me. If you don't think the price is good, then don't buy it. The price of this ammo has increased across the board. The Gun Store in Las Vegas is selling Korean PMC .223 for $0.90/rd, and some unknown steel-core version for $1.23/rd. Great deal, right? But they only have (as of 12 Jan 2013) 100 rds available!  I can't find anywhere that sells Lake City .556 - at ANY price!

And if $4/rd is too steep, give me an offer. I'm up for trades as well.

The PMAG is a lightweight 5.56x45 NATO (.223 Remington) AR15/M16 compatible magazine. It features an advanced impact resistant polymer construction, a pop off Impact/Dust Cover for storage, and an easy to disassemble design with a flared floorplate for positive magazine extraction from pouches. The PMAG 30 utilizes a resilient stainless steel spring for corrosion resistance and a anti tilt, self lubricating follower for increased reliability.

The PMAG MagLevel features transparent windows on both sides of the body and has a painted indicator on the spring for quick determination of approximate rounds remaining in the magazine.
